article.headline: Tennessee Tech 74, Tenn. Martin 72
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 19 points as Tennessee Tech held off Tennessee-Martin 74-72 Thursday night, snapping the Skyhawks' five-game winning streak. Tennessee Tech (17-10, 12-7 Ohio Valley Conference) built a 13-point lead in the second half, 51-38 with 10:57 left. Tennessee-Martin (12-13, 9-10) went on a 12-2 run to tie the game at 63 with 2:28 left. Tennessee-Martin's Jeremy Kelly hit two free throws with 26 seconds left to make it 71-67, and Fisher countered with one for Tech to make it 72-67 with 15 seconds left. The Skyhawks' McClennon Tolliver hit a 3-pointer with four seconds left for the final score. Tech's Belton Rivers had 15 points and Milone Clark had 12, all in the second half. Jared Newson scored 29 for Tennessee-Martin, Kelly had 22 and Will Lewis 10. The Skyhawks stayed close by hitting 28-of-33 free throws.
